\begin_layout Standard
In case of a resolved collision of multiple 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16s$
\end_inset

, the proposed pseudo-parallel reading process is applied.
 A tag receiving its valid 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16$
\end_inset

 replies with its EPC and goes to the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Acknowledged
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 state.
 In contrast, a tag receiving an invalid 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16$
\end_inset

 (e.g.
 valid for another tag) goes to a new state called 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Wait
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 state.
 In the latter state the tag memorizes its 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16$
\end_inset

 until one of the two possibilities occurs: a) receiving an 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

ACK
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command containing its 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16$
\end_inset

.
 In this case the tag replies with its EPC and goes to the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Acknowledged
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 state, b) receiving the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

ACK
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command with wrong 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16$
\end_inset

.
 In this case, the tag remains in the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Wait
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 state waiting for a new command.
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Modified-part-of"

\end_inset

 presents a state diagram with the required modifications of the tag state
 diagram given in figure 6.19 of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "standard"

\end_inset

.
 
