\begin_layout Subsection
Proposed Reader
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The proposed reader applies the normal FSA based on the conventional UHF
 EPCglobal C1 G2 standard, which means that it is able to operate normally
 with conventional tags.
 However, it starts the reading process with a new command called 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Switch
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command to switch the new tags from the conventional mode to the new mode.
 It should be transmitted before the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Query
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command.
 The conventional tags consider the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Switch
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command as an unknown command, but the proposed tags recognize that they
 are working in the new system.
 Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Switch-command"

\end_inset

 provides an example for the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Switch
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command code, which is a 
\begin_inset Formula $16$
\end_inset

 bits command from the future use part of EPCglobal C1 G2 standard (
\shape slanted
cf.

\shape default
 table 6.18 of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "standard"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As discussed before, the EPCglobal C1G2 standard does not support multiple
 acknowledgments per slot.
 On the other hand, the proposed system should benefit from the collision
 resolving capabilities of the modern readers.
 Therefore, the proposed reader has the capability of converting the collided
 slot into a pseudo-parallel successful slot as shown in figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Pesudo-parallel-successful"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The reader starts each slot with a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Query-Rep
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command asking for the 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16$
\end_inset

 of each tag.
 Then, each tag transmits its 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16$
\end_inset

 including one random orthogonal pilot from table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Set-of-8"

\end_inset

.
 In case of a collided slot, the reader executes the following steps:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The reader uses the orthogonal pilots to do channel estimation for the collided
 tags.
 Afterwards, it employs the channel information to recover the collided
 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16s$
\end_inset

 using a MIMO receiver, e.g.
 the receiver proposed in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "2013_orthogonal"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The reader counts the number of recovered 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16s$
\end_inset

 replies in the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Reply Counter
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The reader recognizes whether one of these replies is a conventional pilot
 or not by checking if one of the collided pilots is 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{1}$
\end_inset

(the conventional one) in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Set-of-8"

\end_inset

.
 If yes, the reader considers it as a conventional tag.
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Pesudo_ACK.emf
	lyxscale 20
	width 60page%

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Example of the proposed pseudo-parallel successful slot with parallel 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Query
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command and 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16$
\end_inset

 followed by successive 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

ACK
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 commands and EPCs.
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:Pesudo-parallel-successful"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename psudo_parallel_timing_diagram.emf
	lyxscale 20
	width 70page%
	height 70pheight%

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Example of an inventory round using the proposed reader and 3 collided tags.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:Example-of-an-new-rader_3tags"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

Afterwards, the reader starts acknowledging the collided tags successively
 ordering them from the weakest to the strongest reply.
 The 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Reply Counter
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 counts down with each received EPC from a tag.
 Then, it sends successive 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

ACK
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 commands until the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Reply Counter
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 reaches zero.
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Example-of-an-new-rader_3tags"

\end_inset

 shows an example for a complete inventory round between the proposed reader
 and three collided tags.
 According to figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Example-of-an-new-rader_3tags"

\end_inset

, the reader started an inventory round with a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Switch
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command.
 Thus, the three tags switched to the new mode.
 Then the reader sent a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Query
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command to the tags asking them for their 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16s$
\end_inset

.
 The three tags replied with their 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16s$
\end_inset

 at the first slot and produced collided slot.
 In this case, the reader was able to resolve the three collided 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16s$
\end_inset

.
 Afterwards, the reader applied the pseudo-parallel slot concept to acknowledge
 the three tags during the same slot.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section

\series bold
Performance Analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the conventional DFSA, the reading efficiency is the probability of a
 single tag reply 
\begin_inset Formula $P(R=1)$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $P(R)$
\end_inset

 is the probability that exactly 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 tags are active in one slot.
 It can be presented by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "DFSA_shoute_Random"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
P(R)=\binom{n}{R}\left(\frac{1}{L}\right)^{R}\left(1-\frac{1}{L}\right)^{n-R}.\label{eq:multinomial_with_single acc}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Thus, the reading efficiency of the conventional system is presented by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\eta_{conv}=\left(\frac{n}{L}\right)\left(1-\frac{1}{L}\right)^{n-1}.
\end{equation}

\end_inset

In the proposed system, the reader has the capability to resolve up to 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 collided tags.
 Therefore, the proposed reading efficiency can be presented by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\eta_{proposed}=\sum_{R=1}^{M}P(R)\cdot R_{sol}.\label{eq:parallel_eff}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

For the proposed case, 
\begin_inset Formula $M=8$
\end_inset

 is the number of orthogonal codes which are presented in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Set-of-8"

\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $R_{sol}$
\end_inset

 is the number of recovered tags.
\begin_inset Float table
wide false
sideways false
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Example for unique pilot collision scenarios for up to eight colliding tags
 per slot.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "tab:Collision-scenarios-for"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

