\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The collision recovery capability of the proposed system depends on the
 pilots of the replied tags.
 For the proposed case, the unique scenarios 
\begin_inset Formula $(1+1+...+1)$
\end_inset

 are only considered, i.e.
 if more than one tag uses the same pilot sequence, the reader will not
 be able to resolve this collision.
 Therefore, we have limited number of scenarios.
 Thus, (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:parallel_eff_ot_all"

\end_inset

) considers the effect of the unique scenarios: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\eta_{proposed}=\sum_{R=1}^{M}P(R)\cdot R_{sol}\cdot\sum_{l=1}^{R}P_{S_{l}}(R),\label{eq:parallel_eff_ot_all}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{S_{l}}(R)$
\end_inset

 represents the probability that scenario 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{l}$
\end_inset

 happens.
 It can be calculated from the binomial distribution as explained in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "2013_orthogonal"

\end_inset

.
 Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Collision-scenarios-for"

\end_inset

 shows all values of the unique scenarios 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{S_{l}}(R)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the proposed case, the system is not able to acknowledge the recovered
 tags in parallel.
 It uses the discussed pseudo-parallel method.
 According to figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Pesudo-parallel-successful"

\end_inset

, the conventional successful slot 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{s}$
\end_inset

 is divided into two parts: The first part presents the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Query-Rep
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command and the 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16$
\end_inset

 tag reply 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{s(a)}$
\end_inset

.
 The second part is the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

ACK
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command and the EPC tag reply 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{s(b)}$
\end_inset

.
 Thus, the successful slot time is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
t_{s}=t_{s(a)}+t_{s(b)},\label{eq:successful_slot_time}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{s(a)}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{s(b)}$
\end_inset

 can be expressed by
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
t_{s(a)} & = & T_{qRep}+T_{1}+T_{2}+T_{RN16}.\label{eq:ts(a)}\\
t_{s(b)} & = & T_{ACK}+T_{1}+T_{2}+T_{EPC}.
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:System-Parameters-of"

\end_inset

 shows numerical values from the EPCglobal C1 G2 standard 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "standard"

\end_inset

 as a function of the link pulse-repetition interval 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{pri}$
\end_inset

.
 According to these values, the time of the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Query-Rep
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command and receiving the 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16s$
\end_inset

 presents 
\begin_inset Formula $30\%$
\end_inset

 of the conventional successful slot duration.
 The time of the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

ACK
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command and the EPC tag reply represents 
\begin_inset Formula $70\%$
\end_inset

 of the conventional successful slot duration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the proposed system, the reader sends a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Query
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 command in parallel to all the tags and receives the 
\begin_inset Formula $RN16s$
\end_inset

 in parallel.
 Then, the reader sends successive 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

ACK
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 commands to the resolved tags.
 Therefore, the duration of the proposed pseudo-parallel slot is
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
t_{pseudo}=t_{s(a)}+R_{sol}\cdot t_{s(b)},\label{eq:Pseudo_parallel_slot_duration}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $R_{sol}$
\end_inset

 is the number of recovered tags.
 These tags are acknowledged successively.
 Therefore, the proposed efficiency should include a factor representing
 the effect of the pseudo-parallel spreading in time.
 This factor is called the pseudo-parallel factor 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

.
 According to the numerical values in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:System-Parameters-of"

\end_inset

, it can be expressed by
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\varphi=\left(\frac{1}{0.3+0.7\cdot R_{sol}}\right).\label{eq:pseud_parallel_factor}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Based on the above discussion, the proposed reading efficiency formula consideri
ng the advantages of the new system is formulated as follows:
